description: Various texts containing words related to "cocoa", "coconut", "coco", and "coca", likely referring to cocoa, coconut, and cocaine, often in contexts of food, health, or names of companies and products.

The text features words related to various substances, including methamphetamine, crack cocaine, and other stimulants, as well as prescription medications and chemicals, often in the context of drug use and abuse.
References to substance use, mainly smoking and drug consumption, including the use of specific substances like marijuana and cocaine.
The text features references to various controlled substances, including cocaine and other drugs, often in the context of crime, addiction, and medical or scientific discussions.

The token "co" often appears in proper nouns, including company names, names of people with "Coch" or "Cocoa" as part of their surnames, or as a part of the term "-cocoon", and "co" is also present in the chemical term "Cocaine", it also appears as "co" in the term "Cocoa", also as "co" in the phrase "Cocina".
